<BaseLayout
  title="About — SEOplant"
  description="SEOplant is an open-source AI Programmatic SEO Platform. We believe SEO tools should build sites, not just analyze them."
>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:720px;">

      <h1>About SEOplant</h1>

      <p style="font-size:1.2rem; color:var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
        SEOplant was born from a simple observation: <strong>every AI website builder is terrible at SEO, and every SEO tool can't build a website.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>The Gap We Fill</h2>
      <p>In 2024-2025, dozens of "AI website builders" launched. Durable, 10Web, Wix AI, Framer AI. They can generate a website in 30 seconds. But none of them understand SEO — they don't do keyword research, don't analyze competitors, don't generate topic clusters, don't build programmatic content.</p>
      <p>On the other side, SEO tools like Byword, Surfer SEO, and Frase are great at content strategy and keyword analysis. But after they give you a content plan, you're on your own — you still need to build the website, configure the server, set up Schema markup, and deploy everything.</p>
      <p><strong>SEOplant connects these two worlds.</strong> It's the first platform that takes a keyword as input and produces a live, SEO-optimized website as output. Not just content — the entire site.</p>

      <h2>Open Source First</h2>
      <p>We believe the core technology should be open. The five pipeline modules — competitor intelligence, SEO engine, design intelligence, site builder, and deployer — are all MIT licensed. You can inspect, modify, and self-host everything.</p>
      <p>The cloud platform (seoplant.io) adds real SEO data from DataForSEO, AI agent orchestration, and programmatic SEO at scale. But you're never locked in — your generated site is a standard Astro project that you can deploy anywhere.</p>

      <h2>Philosophy</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No vendor lock-in.</strong> Your code, your server, your data. Always.</li>
        <li><strong>SEO-first, not design-first.</strong> Pretty sites that don't rank are invisible.</li>
        <li><strong>Automate the boring.</strong> Keyword research, schema markup, internal linking, deployment — machines should do this.</li>
        <li><strong>Human creativity on top.</strong> AI handles the heavy lifting; humans add soul, nuance, and strategy.</li>
      </ul>

